        "created_at": "2018-06-06T22:06:58.945Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had some success by replacing FoundationDB with LMDB to emulate a distributed system in a single process (for demoing, local development mode and fast simulated tests).</p>\n<p>Of course, this didn\u2019t replace proper FDB-based tests (these still had to be run) but helped to establish a quick feedback. Especially, if you use ASYNC flushing for the LMDB.</p>",
