        "id": 1435,
        "name": "David Scherer",
        "username": "dave",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/dave/{size}/89_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-08T21:46:33.954Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A trick that can work for many unit tests is to create a transaction, set the read version to 1, clear the entire database, do your unit test using the transaction, and then just don\u2019t commit it. If you do this right, you don\u2019t even need a database to connect to, since all reads can be satisfied locally by the fdb client and the writes are rolled back!</p>",
